# Patient Match Service

## Onboarding Document

## 13/11/2019

1. 1.Objective

The intent of this onboarding guide is to provide a simple, high level guide for planning and implementing Patient Match Service for any of the Phytel project.

**Intended Audience**

This guide will be helpful for any of the team who would like to leverage Patient Match Service for their projects and will cover important steps or considerations to ensure a successful deployment.

1. 2.What is Patient Match Service?

The purpose of the patient matching service is to match the incoming patient records coming via an external source - Discharge Summaries, Claims Data etc. against the records present in Phytel Database. This is done based on a weighted approach algorithm which marks an incoming record as a Match or Not Matched based on the generated confidence level.

**Key Elements:**

- **Property File –** Used for defining different algorithms, related criteria&#39;s &amp; their execution sequence and finally the resulting confidence interval.
- **Algorithm -** Patient Match Service supports defining multiple algorithms in the system where each of the algorithm should have a unique name. The same name is sent as a parameter each time the request is made to patient match service.
- **Criteria –** Collection of attributes, resulting confidence interval and the SQL query that gets executed in Phytel Database.
- **Attributes –** Key value pairs that are part of the criteria&#39;s and are used for patient match.
- **Patient Data –** The data that is received from the calling application that should be used for patient match
- **Contract Name -** The name of the application which will use patient match service.
- **Database / Data Store –** The schema which is used for patient match against the ingested patient data

1. c)Define Each Algorithm Properties

Algorithm properties is divided into:

1. a) **Name:  ** A unique name should be defined for each of the algorithm – the same name will be used in the request call as well.

** **.

1. b) **Enabled Flag:  **  If the status is turned off then that algorithm cannot be used in the request call.

1. c) **Criteria Sequence:  **  Here for each of the algorithm you defined the criteria&#39;s to be used and their sequence in which the execution should happen.



| **Property Name** | **Description** | **Default Value** | **Sample Value** | **Configurable** | **Data Type** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Algorithm.Claim\_ingestion** | This is name of algorithm | NA | NA | Y | String |
| **Enabled** | This is a flag used for turning on/off an algorithm. | True | True, False | Y | Boolean |
| **Criteria.Sequence** | Specify the criteria&#39;s number and their order of execution | NA | 1,2,3 | Y | List |

1. e)Define Criteria&#39;s and its properties

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Figure 7: Max Confidence Value

Building blocks of Criteria:

1. a) **Criteria Number:** Each of the criteria in the property file is given a number with which its referred in the Algorithm. We have kept it sequential. When you are adding a new criterion make sure to use a unique number which is not used elsewhere.
2. b) **Attributes:**
For every Criteria first we need to define attributes, these attributes should be part of PatientData. To add new criteria:

1.
  1. Check if the new attribute is available as part of PatientData (Defined in swagger contract)
  2. If it&#39;s already present, go ahead and directly add the attribute to the new criteria.
  3. If it&#39;s not, it requires a change in the PatientData.  This is done by changing PatientResource class in the project library.

1. c) **Confidence Value:**

For every criterion, we need to define the confidence value that needs to be returned.

1. d) **SQL Query**

SQL query that gets executed in the system for patient Match



| **Property Name** | **Description** | **Default Value** | **Sample Value** | **Configurable** | **Data Type** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Criteria.1** | Unique Number given to each of the criteria | NA | NA | Y | Number |
| **Attributes** | List of attributes that are part of the criteria | NA | Patient.identifier, patient.sourceId | Y | List |
| **Confidence** | Resulting confidence interval if this criteria is satisfied. This is a combination of confidence max value and some number | NA | ${confidence.max} + 10 | Y | Number |
| **ContactEntities.sqlquery** | The SQL query that needs to be executed if the data store name in the received request is &quot;contact entities&quot; | NA | NA | Y | SQL Query |
| **patientMPI.sqlquery** | The SQL query that needs to be executed if the data store name in the received request is &quot;patientMPI&quot; | NA | NA | Y | SQL Query |
